Currently if the user creates a different status and transitions an issue (that is in a completed sprint) or change the project Workflow, the historical data will be affected. For example, the sprint report will show the completed issue as still incomplete.

As an Agile Administrator, I would like to change the status in my workflow and the Agile plugin recognise all these changes and adjust it in the historical data on its reports.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-11833].
  {panel}

As a user, I would like to be able search by the values in the "Epic Link" field from the _basic_ mode in the issue navigator.

At the moment, this is not supported and I am prompted to use _advanced_ search instead.

This was cloned because it had the status resolved, but still it is not possible!

{code:sql}
# SELECT * FROM AO_60DB71_SPRINT;
CLOSED | COMPLETE_DATE |   END_DATE    | ID |   NAME   | RAPID_VIEW_ID | SEQUENCE | STARTED |  START_DATE   
		--------+---------------+---------------+----+----------+---------------+----------+---------+---------------
 f      |               | 1425461760000 |  1 | Sprint 1 |             2 |          | t       | 1424252191171{code}

The sprint table is still referencing to deleted board "rapid_view_id = 2". It's not clear what is the purpose of the RAPID_VIEW_ID in this table.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Software Cloud*. Using *JIRA Software Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JSWSERVER-11697].
  {panel}

h3. Steps to Reproduce:
# Install JIRA and JIRA Agile;
# Create the DEMO project;
# Create a scrum board for the DEMO project;
# And rename the user used to create the board (or any board administrator).

h3. Expected Behavior
The user's full name would be displayed in the "Manage Boards" view.

h3. Actual Behavior
JIRA Agile doesn't handle the renamed username, and instead of displaying the user's full name displays 'Anonymous' in the "Manage Boards" screen.
